Q3/- What is the difference between SOAP and REST ?


Soap=>
     1) soap(Single object access protocol) is a XML based protocol to communicate between 
      client application to the server application.
     2)it is also platform and language independent.
     3)creating a webService application using SOAP are havay weight application 
      

Rest=>
     1)using REST(Representational state transfer) to create a webServices with the 
       required operations(functionalities and expose them through the http protocol and
       allow then to be accessed by the client with the help of http protocol without 
       any extra binding classes and XML files.
     2)crating a webServices application using REST are light weight application.
      
     
      
    
      